{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":841,"text":"I have a confession to make."},{"time":4968,"text":"But first, I want you to make\na little confession to me."},{"time":11779,"text":"In the past year,\nI want you to just raise your hand"},{"time":14557,"text":"if you've experienced\nrelatively little stress."},{"time":17971,"text":"Anyone?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20604,"text":"How about a moderate amount of stress?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23840,"text":"Who has experienced a lot of stress?"},{"time":26441,"text":"Yeah. Me too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28849,"text":"But that is not my confession."},{"time":30997,"text":"My confession is this:"},{"time":32782,"text":"I am a health psychologist,"},{"time":34803,"text":"and my mission is to help people\nbe happier and healthier."},{"time":39699,"text":"But I fear that something\nI've been teaching"},{"time":42926,"text":"for the last 10 years\nis doing more harm than good,"},{"time":47254,"text":"and it has to do with stress."},{"time":49826,"text":"For years I've been telling people,\nstress makes you sick."},{"time":52853,"text":"It increases the risk of everything\nfrom the common cold"},{"time":55748,"text":"to cardiovascular disease."},{"time":58134,"text":"Basically, I've turned stress\ninto the enemy."},{"time":62383,"text":"But I have changed my mind about stress,"},{"time":65095,"text":"and today, I want to change yours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69010,"text":"Let me start with the study\nthat made me rethink"},{"time":71390,"text":"my whole approach to stress."},{"time":74004,"text":"This study tracked 30,000 adults\nin the United States for eight years,"},{"time":78663,"text":"and they started by asking people,"},{"time":81190,"text":"\"How much stress have you\nexperienced in the last year?\""},{"time":85088,"text":"They also asked,"},{"time":86652,"text":"\"Do you believe that stress\nis harmful for your health?\""},{"time":92430,"text":"And then they used public death records\nto find out who died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96010,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97215,"text":"Okay."},{"time":99037,"text":"Some bad news first."},{"time":101211,"text":"People who experienced a lot of stress\nin the previous year"},{"time":104636,"text":"had a 43 percent increased risk of dying."},{"time":108612,"text":"But that was only true for the people"},{"time":112395,"text":"who also believed that stress\nis harmful for your health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116056,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118840,"text":"People who experienced a lot of stress"},{"time":121140,"text":"but did not view stress as harmful"},{"time":123104,"text":"were no more likely to die."},{"time":124805,"text":"In fact, they had the lowest risk of dying"},{"time":128372,"text":"of anyone in the study,"},{"time":129696,"text":"including people\nwho had relatively little stress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132896,"text":"Now the researchers estimated\nthat over the eight years"},{"time":135540,"text":"they were tracking deaths,"},{"time":137134,"text":"182,000 Americans died prematurely,"},{"time":140334,"text":"not from stress,"},{"time":141796,"text":"but from the belief\nthat stress is bad for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145001,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146257,"text":"That is over 20,000 deaths a year."},{"time":149931,"text":"Now, if that estimate is correct,"},{"time":152759,"text":"that would make\nbelieving stress is bad for you"},{"time":155022,"text":"the 15th largest cause of death\nin the United States last year,"},{"time":159117,"text":"killing more people than skin cancer,\nHIV/AIDS and homicide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165172,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167311,"text":"You can see why this study freaked me out."},{"time":170136,"text":"Here I've been spending\nso much energy telling people"},{"time":174209,"text":"stress is bad for your health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177090,"text":"So this study got me wondering:"},{"time":178786,"text":"Can changing how you think\nabout stress make you healthier?"},{"time":182882,"text":"And here the science says yes."},{"time":184726,"text":"When you change your mind about stress,"},{"time":186808,"text":"you can change\nyour body's response to stress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190084,"text":"Now to explain how this works,"},{"time":192441,"text":"I want you all to pretend\nthat you are participants"},{"time":195322,"text":"in a study designed to stress you out."},{"time":197929,"text":"It's called the social stress test."},{"time":200613,"text":"You come into the laboratory,"},{"time":202667,"text":"and you're told you have to give"},{"time":204662,"text":"a five-minute impromptu speech\non your personal weaknesses"},{"time":209301,"text":"to a panel of expert evaluators\nsitting right in front of you,"},{"time":212958,"text":"and to make sure you feel the pressure,"},{"time":214840,"text":"there are bright lights\nand a camera in your face,"},{"time":217811,"text":"kind of like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219294,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220476,"text":"And the evaluators have been trained"},{"time":223380,"text":"to give you discouraging,\nnon-verbal feedback,"},{"time":227096,"text":"like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233334,"text":"(Exhales)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":234359,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237264,"text":"Now that you're sufficiently demoralized,"},{"time":239356,"text":"time for part two: a math test."},{"time":242156,"text":"And unbeknownst to you,"},{"time":244257,"text":"the experimenter has been trained\nto harass you during it."},{"time":248285,"text":"Now we're going to all do this together."},{"time":250659,"text":"It's going to be fun."},{"time":252404,"text":"For me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253451,"text":"Okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254492,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255723,"text":"I want you all to count backwards from 996"},{"time":259746,"text":"in increments of seven."},{"time":261138,"text":"You're going to do this out loud,"},{"time":262766,"text":"as fast as you can,"},{"time":264774,"text":"starting with 996."},{"time":266890,"text":"Go!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267952,"text":"(Audience counting)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":269333,"text":"Go faster. Faster please."},{"time":272146,"text":"You're going too slow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273536,"text":"(Audience counting)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274598,"text":"Stop. Stop, stop, stop."},{"time":276114,"text":"That guy made a mistake."},{"time":277544,"text":"We are going to have to start\nall over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279766,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280791,"text":"You're not very good at this, are you?"},{"time":283027,"text":"Okay, so you get the idea."},{"time":284501,"text":"If you were actually in this study,"},{"time":286340,"text":"you'd probably be a little stressed out."},{"time":288286,"text":"Your heart might be pounding,"},{"time":289825,"text":"you might be breathing faster,\nmaybe breaking out into a sweat."},{"time":293229,"text":"And normally, we interpret\nthese physical changes as anxiety"},{"time":297825,"text":"or signs that we aren't coping\nvery well with the pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301142,"text":"But what if you viewed them instead"},{"time":303015,"text":"as signs that your body was energized,"},{"time":305362,"text":"was preparing you to meet this challenge?"},{"time":309064,"text":"Now that is exactly\nwhat participants were told"},{"time":311650,"text":"in a study conducted\nat Harvard University."},{"time":314596,"text":"Before they went\nthrough the social stress test,"},{"time":317417,"text":"they were taught to rethink\ntheir stress response as helpful."},{"time":320623,"text":"That pounding heart\nis preparing you for action."},{"time":324408,"text":"If you're breathing faster,\nit's no problem."},{"time":326761,"text":"It's getting more oxygen to your brain."},{"time":329846,"text":"And participants who learned to view\nthe stress response"},{"time":332543,"text":"as helpful for their performance,"},{"time":334780,"text":"well, they were less stressed out,\nless anxious, more confident,"},{"time":338287,"text":"but the most fascinating finding to me"},{"time":340380,"text":"was how their physical\nstress response changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343906,"text":"Now, in a typical stress response,"},{"time":345655,"text":"your heart rate goes up,"},{"time":347471,"text":"and your blood vessels\nconstrict like this."},{"time":352343,"text":"And this is one of the reasons\nthat chronic stress"},{"time":354950,"text":"is sometimes associated\nwith cardiovascular disease."},{"time":357809,"text":"It's not really healthy to be\nin this state all the time."},{"time":361518,"text":"But in the study,"},{"time":362630,"text":"when participants viewed\ntheir stress response as helpful,"},{"time":365661,"text":"their blood vessels\nstayed relaxed like this."},{"time":369176,"text":"Their heart was still pounding,"},{"time":370977,"text":"but this is a much healthier\ncardiovascular profile."},{"time":373728,"text":"It actually looks a lot like what happens"},{"time":376383,"text":"in moments of joy and courage."},{"time":381391,"text":"Over a lifetime of stressful experiences,"},{"time":383935,"text":"this one biological change"},{"time":387125,"text":"could be the difference"},{"time":388429,"text":"between a stress-induced\nheart attack at age 50"},{"time":391433,"text":"and living well into your 90s."},{"time":394356,"text":"And this is really what the new\nscience of stress reveals,"},{"time":397441,"text":"that how you think about stress matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401197,"text":"So my goal as a health\npsychologist has changed."},{"time":404110,"text":"I no longer want\nto get rid of your stress."},{"time":406272,"text":"I want to make you better at stress."},{"time":409230,"text":"And we just did a little intervention."},{"time":411935,"text":"If you raised your hand and said"},{"time":413483,"text":"you'd had a lot of stress\nin the last year,"},{"time":415552,"text":"we could have saved your life,"},{"time":417395,"text":"because hopefully the next time\nyour heart is pounding from stress,"},{"time":420946,"text":"you're going to remember this talk"},{"time":422793,"text":"and you're going to think to yourself,"},{"time":424955,"text":"this is my body helping me\nrise to this challenge."},{"time":430129,"text":"And when you view stress in that way,"},{"time":432468,"text":"your body believes you,"},{"time":434525,"text":"and your stress response\nbecomes healthier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438204,"text":"Now I said I have over a decade\nof demonizing stress"},{"time":442380,"text":"to redeem myself from,"},{"time":444354,"text":"so we are going to do\none more intervention."},{"time":446964,"text":"I want to tell you"},{"time":448092,"text":"about one of the most under-appreciated\naspects of the stress response,"},{"time":451987,"text":"and the idea is this:"},{"time":453846,"text":"Stress makes you social."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457266,"text":"To understand this side of stress,"},{"time":459050,"text":"we need to talk about a hormone, oxytocin,"},{"time":461917,"text":"and I know oxytocin has already gotten\nas much hype as a hormone can get."},{"time":466865,"text":"It even has its own cute nickname,\nthe cuddle hormone,"},{"time":470204,"text":"because it's released\nwhen you hug someone."},{"time":472890,"text":"But this is a very small part\nof what oxytocin is involved in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477572,"text":"Oxytocin is a neuro-hormone."},{"time":479870,"text":"It fine-tunes\nyour brain's social instincts."},{"time":483978,"text":"It primes you to do things"},{"time":485975,"text":"that strengthen close relationships."},{"time":489486,"text":"Oxytocin makes you crave physical contact\nwith your friends and family."},{"time":494334,"text":"It enhances your empathy."},{"time":495920,"text":"It even makes you more willing\nto help and support"},{"time":498628,"text":"the people you care about."},{"time":501672,"text":"Some people have even suggested\nwe should snort oxytocin..."},{"time":507179,"text":"to become more compassionate and caring."},{"time":511340,"text":"But here's what most people\ndon't understand about oxytocin."},{"time":516164,"text":"It's a stress hormone."},{"time":519130,"text":"Your pituitary gland pumps this stuff out"},{"time":522248,"text":"as part of the stress response."},{"time":523796,"text":"It's as much a part\nof your stress response"},{"time":526047,"text":"as the adrenaline that makes\nyour heart pound."},{"time":530271,"text":"And when oxytocin is released\nin the stress response,"},{"time":532969,"text":"it is motivating you to seek support."},{"time":536330,"text":"Your biological stress response"},{"time":538383,"text":"is nudging you to tell\nsomeone how you feel,"},{"time":541926,"text":"instead of bottling it up."},{"time":544306,"text":"Your stress response wants\nto make sure you notice"},{"time":547410,"text":"when someone else\nin your life is struggling"},{"time":549729,"text":"so that you can support each other."},{"time":552299,"text":"When life is difficult,"},{"time":553983,"text":"your stress response wants you\nto be surrounded"},{"time":558594,"text":"by people who care about you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561158,"text":"Okay, so how is knowing this side\nof stress going to make you healthier?"},{"time":565686,"text":"Well, oxytocin doesn't only act\non your brain."},{"time":568271,"text":"It also acts on your body,"},{"time":570662,"text":"and one of its main roles in your body"},{"time":572861,"text":"is to protect your cardiovascular system\nfrom the effects of stress."},{"time":577956,"text":"It's a natural anti-inflammatory."},{"time":580524,"text":"It also helps your blood vessels\nstay relaxed during stress."},{"time":583969,"text":"But my favorite effect on the body\nis actually on the heart."},{"time":587366,"text":"Your heart has receptors for this hormone,"},{"time":591328,"text":"and oxytocin helps heart cells regenerate"},{"time":594806,"text":"and heal from any stress-induced damage."},{"time":598774,"text":"This stress hormone\nstrengthens your heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603591,"text":"And the cool thing\nis that all of these physical benefits"},{"time":606857,"text":"of oxytocin are enhanced\nby social contact and social support."},{"time":611907,"text":"So when you reach out\nto others under stress,"},{"time":614826,"text":"either to seek support\nor to help someone else,"},{"time":618099,"text":"you release more of this hormone,"},{"time":620107,"text":"your stress response becomes healthier,"},{"time":622369,"text":"and you actually recover\nfaster from stress."},{"time":625658,"text":"I find this amazing,"},{"time":627801,"text":"that your stress response\nhas a built-in mechanism"},{"time":631729,"text":"for stress resilience,"},{"time":634634,"text":"and that mechanism is human connection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639174,"text":"I want to finish by telling you\nabout one more study."},{"time":642398,"text":"And listen up, because this study\ncould also save a life."},{"time":646651,"text":"This study tracked about 1,000 adults\nin the United States,"},{"time":649930,"text":"and they ranged in age from 34 to 93,"},{"time":654093,"text":"and they started the study by asking,"},{"time":656362,"text":"\"How much stress have you\nexperienced in the last year?\""},{"time":660779,"text":"They also asked,"},{"time":662304,"text":"\"How much time have you spent\nhelping out friends, neighbors,"},{"time":666963,"text":"people in your community?\""},{"time":670133,"text":"And then they used public records\nfor the next five years"},{"time":672908,"text":"to find out who died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675531,"text":"Okay, so the bad news first:"},{"time":678212,"text":"For every major stressful life experience,"},{"time":681171,"text":"like financial difficulties\nor family crisis,"},{"time":684220,"text":"that increased the risk\nof dying by 30 percent."},{"time":688451,"text":"But -- and I hope you\nare expecting a \"but\" by now --"},{"time":692445,"text":"but that wasn't true for everyone."},{"time":694876,"text":"People who spent time caring for others"},{"time":698538,"text":"showed absolutely no stress-related\nincrease in dying."},{"time":703065,"text":"Zero."},{"time":704738,"text":"Caring created resilience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708233,"text":"And so we see once again"},{"time":709716,"text":"that the harmful effects\nof stress on your health"},{"time":712354,"text":"are not inevitable."},{"time":714578,"text":"How you think and how you act"},{"time":717038,"text":"can transform your experience of stress."},{"time":720998,"text":"When you choose to view\nyour stress response as helpful,"},{"time":725936,"text":"you create the biology of courage."},{"time":730547,"text":"And when you choose to connect\nwith others under stress,"},{"time":733988,"text":"you can create resilience."},{"time":737606,"text":"Now I wouldn't necessarily ask\nfor more stressful experiences in my life,"},{"time":743160,"text":"but this science has given me\na whole new appreciation for stress."},{"time":749237,"text":"Stress gives us access to our hearts."},{"time":753897,"text":"The compassionate heart\nthat finds joy and meaning"},{"time":757580,"text":"in connecting with others,"},{"time":759118,"text":"and yes, your pounding physical heart,"},{"time":762680,"text":"working so hard to give you\nstrength and energy."},{"time":767945,"text":"And when you choose to view\nstress in this way,"},{"time":771288,"text":"you're not just getting better at stress,"},{"time":773800,"text":"you're actually making\na pretty profound statement."},{"time":777627,"text":"You're saying that you can trust yourself\nto handle life's challenges."},{"time":783928,"text":"And you're remembering\nthat you don't have to face them alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789659,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790733,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":800014,"text":"Chris Anderson: This is kind\nof amazing, what you're telling us."},{"time":803086,"text":"It seems amazing to me\nthat a belief about stress"},{"time":807017,"text":"can make so much difference\nto someone's life expectancy."},{"time":811500,"text":"How would that extend to advice,"},{"time":813726,"text":"like, if someone is making\na lifestyle choice"},{"time":815893,"text":"between, say, a stressful job\nand a non-stressful job,"},{"time":819772,"text":"does it matter which way they go?"},{"time":822453,"text":"It's equally wise to go\nfor the stressful job"},{"time":824982,"text":"so long as you believe\nthat you can handle it, in some sense?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":827919,"text":"KM: Yeah, and one thing\nwe know for certain"},{"time":830203,"text":"is that chasing meaning\nis better for your health"},{"time":832611,"text":"than trying to avoid discomfort."},{"time":834215,"text":"And so I would say that's really\nthe best way to make decisions,"},{"time":837287,"text":"is go after what it is\nthat creates meaning in your life"},{"time":840034,"text":"and then trust yourself to handle\nthe stress that follows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843758,"text":"CA: Thank you so much, Kelly.\nIt's pretty cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846154,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}